      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Simply put, indemnification is a contractual promise where one party agrees to cover the losses or damages of the other party under certain circumstances. If you cause a problem or something goes wrong because of your work, this clause determines who pays for the resulting legal fees or settlements. Essentially, it shifts the financial risk associated with specific risks from one party to the other.",
